cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.AI 

This paper proposes a deep learning strategy to leverage social information of trust and distrust relationships in recommender systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the top-k recommendation task, which suggests a possible fit with cs.SOC (Social and Societal Computing). Finally, the use of multiple ranking criteria and the proposed social negative sampling strategy may also relate to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
